## TRACK C — HLX-LS PATCH SCHEMA

### C1: Define Patch Contracts

**Contract 200:** `PatchManifest`
````
@0: TEXT     — patch_name
@1: TEXT     — timestamp (ISO 8601)
@2: TEXT     — version_transition ("v1.2 → v1.3")
@3: HANDLE   — source_capsule_ref (optional)
@4: ARRAY    — operations (array of Contract 201)
````

**Contract 201:** `PatchOperation`
````
@0: TEXT     — op_type ("ADD" | "MODIFY" | "DELETE")
@1: TEXT     — target_path (relative to capsule root)
@2: HANDLE   — content_ref (collapsed LC stream of file contents)
@3: TEXT     — expected_hash (SHA256 of result, optional)
````

### C2: Produce HLX-LS Patch Program

**File:** `patches/v1.3/hlx_v13_patch.hlx`
````hlx
⟠ hlx_v13_patch {
  ◇ manifest() {
    ⊢ meta = {200:{
      @0: "HLX v1.3 Conformance + Tooling Patch",
      @1: "2025-12-13T12:00:00Z",
      @2: "v1.2 → v1.3",
      @3: ⟁hlx_v12_capsule₀
    }};
    
    ⊢ ops = 🜃
      {201:{@0: "ADD", @1: "tools/hlx_exporter.py", @2: ⟁exporter_py₀}}
      {201:{@0: "ADD", @1: "tools/hlx_verifier.py", @2: ⟁verifier_py₀}}
      {201:{@0: "MODIFY", @1: "hlx_runtime_conformance.json", @2: ⟁conformance_v13₀}}
      {201:{@0: "ADD", @1: "fixtures/lc12/valid_envelope.json", @2: ⟁fixture_valid₀}}
      {201:{@0: "ADD", @1: "fixtures/lc12/valid_payload.lc", @2: ⟁payload_valid₀}}
      {201:{@0: "ADD", @1: "fixtures/lc12/tampered_payload.lc", @2: ⟁payload_tampered₀}}
      {201:{@0: "ADD", @1: "README_v1.3.md", @2: ⟁readme_delta₀}}
    🜄;
    
    ↩ ⚳ patch_table v13 {200:{@0: meta, @1: ops}};
  }
}
````

**File:** `patches/v1.3/hlx_v13_patch.hlxl` (bijective ASCII)

### C3: Wrap in LC_12 Envelope

The patch program + all referenced handles are collapsed to LC-B, chunked, Merkle-hashed, and wrapped in an LC_12 envelope.

